About Standard Chartered
We are a leading international bank focused on helping people and companies prosper across Asia, Africa and the Middle East.
To us, good performance is about much more than turning a profit. &nbsp;It's about showing how you embody our valued behaviours - do the right thing, better together and never settle - as well as our brand promise, Here for good.
We're committed to promoting equality in the workplace and creating an inclusive and flexible culture - one where everyone can realise their full potential and make a positive contribution to our organisation. This in turn helps us to provide better support to our broad client base.
The Role Responsibilities &amp; Our Ideal Candidate

  Manage and govern the FDC as &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;an operating function, with necessary governance and reporting.
  Manage delivery of common &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;data initiatives (in line with the objectives of the Functions CIO Data &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Council - FDC) for CIO Functions. This includes delivery of cross-cutting &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;themes to align to the data strategy &amp; data design principles.
  The cross-cutting initiatives &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;include (but not limited to) maintenance of data lineage documentation in &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BAU, consistent usage of DQ tooling, coordination of updates to Current &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&amp; Target State Architecture diagrams amongst others.
  Enable definition and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;maintenance of the data strategy across Risk, Finance &amp; CFCC to align &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;data principles, strategies for data sourcing, tooling &amp; DMF &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;compliance.
  Coordinate with various &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;stakeholders in CIO Functions, Architecture, CDO &amp; Upstream Change &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Governance Committees (as required) to implement the objectives of the &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FDC.
  Be the primary face-off into &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the Functions Technology Council (FTC) to support the FDC’s agenda &amp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;enable necessary approvals from FDC. This includes liaison between the FTC &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&amp; the core members of the FDC to review requests, manage the challenge &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&amp; approval processes.
  Establish the mechanisms, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;templates &amp; processes for ongoing review &amp; assessment of CIO &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;responsibilities on BCBS239 compliance.
  Manage the ongoing cadence &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;process to liaise with the relevant CIO Domain Leads to assess status of &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;deliveries &amp; flight path to achieve the BCBS239 objectives &amp; plans
  Liaise with the BCBS239 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Central Oversight Programme &amp; the relevant stakeholders to define / &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;enhance the process &amp; tooling to support the yearly self-assessment &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;processes; establish the workflow &amp; processes for the self-assessment &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;processes covering CIO paragraphs
  Own the BCBS239 paragraphs &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;on behalf of CIO &amp;
  Provide a single face-off &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;into the various stakeholders for CIO, including BCBS239 Programme Teams, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Reporting, Risk &amp; Finance Infrastructure / Change Teams &amp; the &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;DQ Teams requiring coordination &amp; enablement of compliance with the &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CIO paragraphs

